articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A 40-second clip of an old interview in which Russian mercenary boss Yevgeny Prigozhin said he would rather be killed than lie to his country, and talked about a plane disintegrating in the sky, unleashed a flood of online theorizing on Sunday about his presumed death.
articles.title: Old video sparks wild theories on fate of Russia's Prigozhin

articles.author: Thomas Escritt
articles.description: An antisemitic flyer distributed at a German secondary school more than three decades ago is at the centre of a dispute that threatens to engulf Hubert Aiwanger, deputy premier of Bavaria, ahead of a regional election in the state later this year.
articles.title: Decades-old antisemitic flyer threatens to upend German state vote

articles.author: Jean Loobentz Cesar
articles.description: Hundreds of people are crammed into small white tents in the courtyard of a sports center in the Haitian capital, Port-au-Prince, drying clothes on the access ramps and washing their children in small, plastic tubs.
articles.title: Haitians shelter in sports center as fresh attacks displace nearly 9,000

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: One person died and 46 were hospitalized after two explosions at a liquefied petroleum gas station in the Romanian town of Crevedia, near the capital Bucharest on Saturday.
articles.title: One person dead, 46 injured after explosions at Romanian gas station

articles.author: Howard Schneider
articles.description: U.S. trade has shifted away from China due to policies enacted by the Biden and Trump administrations, but U.S. reliance on China-linked supply chains has not necessarily been reduced and consumers have faced higher costs, according to new research presented on Saturday at a Federal Reserve economic symposium.
articles.title: Trump, Biden policies shifted trade from China at a cost, study shows

articles.author: Thomas Escritt
articles.description: Despite the murders of four of her colleagues for their reporting, Russian journalist Elena Kostyuchenko never considered she had been poisoned when she fell ill on a train to Berlin.
articles.title: Exiled Russian journalist describes 'poisoning' ordeal on German train

articles.author: Gerauds Wilfried Obangome
articles.description: Gabon's government blocked internet access and imposed a curfew on Saturday after an election marked by major voting delays, as the opposition cried foul over a poll they hoped would halt President Ali Bongo's bid to extend his family's 56-year grip on power.
articles.title: Gabon cuts internet, imposes curfew amid election voting delays

articles.author: Jasper Ward
articles.description: A shooting at a Dollar General store in Jacksonville, Florida, left four people dead on Saturday, Fox News reported.
articles.title: Four people dead in Dollar General shooting in Jacksonville

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Former President Donald Trump has raised nearly $20 million in the past three weeks, a period that roughly coincides with his indictment in federal and state cases connected to his false claims that the 2020 election was stolen from him, Trump's campaign spokesman said on Saturday,
articles.title: Trump raised $7.1 million since he was booked Thursday at an Atlanta jail

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: An aircraft incident involving U.S. military personnel occurred mid-morning on Sunday during an exercise in Australia's Northern Territory, Australia's Defence Ministry said.
articles.title: Aircraft with US military personnel crashes in Australia - defence ministry
